                "role": "assistant",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "The project is fully scaffolded. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Java MCP Server** (`src/main/java/io/frameworkdocs/mcp/`):\n- `DocSearchTools.java` — MCP `searchDocs` tool with synonym expansion, metadata boosting, framework filtering\n- `FrameworkDetector.java` — auto-detects 15 frameworks from project files (go.mod, pom.xml, package.json, Cargo.toml, etc.)\n- `EmbeddingModelLoader.java` — async BGE Small EN v1.5 model loading\n- `ContainerManager.java` — PgVector embedding store connection\n- `SqlLoader.java` — schema readiness check\n- `StartupObserver.java` — warm-up logging on startup\n\n**Docker** (`docker/` + `Dockerfile`):\n- Single container running PostgreSQL 17 + pgvector + Java MCP server\n- `entrypoint.sh` starts PG then the Java server\n- `init.sql` creates the schema, `zz-index.sql` creates ivfflat index after data load\n\n**Python Ingestion Pipeline** (`ingestion/`):\n- `scraper.py` — `DocPage` dataclass + `BaseScraper` ABC\n- `chunker.py` — recursive text splitting (500 chars, 50 overlap)\n- `embedder.py` — BGE Small EN v1.5 via sentence-transformers\n- `sql_writer.py` — generates INSERT statements for pgvector\n- `cli.py` — Click CLI with `scrape` and `scrape-all` commands\n- 3 scrapers: Go Fiber, FastAPI, Spring Boot\n\n**To build and run:**\n```bash\n# 1. Ingest docs\ncd ingestion && pip install -e . && python -m src.cli scrape-all\n\n# 2. Build server\ncd .. && ./mvnw package -DskipTests -Dquarkus.package.jar.type=uber-jar\n\n# 3. Build & run Docker\ndocker build -t framework-docs-mcp:latest .\ndocker run -i --rm framework-docs-mcp:latest\n```\n\nNote: The `pom.xml` uses Quarkus 3.23.3 and langchain4j 1.0.0-beta3 (the latest available stable versions — the PRD specifies future versions that don't exist yet). You'll want to update these when those versions are released."
                  }
                ],
                "meta": {
                  "timestamp": 1781778729
                }
              }
            },
