        "message_id": "55a0ef3e-7f43-417b-b4ad-59ce639f1b2b",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Done. Here's what was added:\n\n**Requirements** — 4 new entries in the Technologies table:\n- `spring-framework` — Spring Framework 7 (IoC, AOP, WebMVC, WebFlux, transactions)\n- `spring-security` — Spring Security 7 (auth, OAuth2, CSRF, CORS)\n- `spring-data` — Spring Data 2024 (repositories, JPA, query methods)\n- `spring-cloud` — Spring Cloud 2024 (Gateway, Config, Circuit Breaker, Stream, Feign)\n\n**Code changes:**\n- 4 new scrapers in `ingestion/src/scrapers/` (spring_framework, spring_security, spring_data, spring_cloud)\n- Registered in `cli.py`\n- `DocSearchTools.java` tool description updated to list Spring ecosystem\n- `FrameworkDetector.java` now detects spring-cloud, spring-security, spring-data in pom.xml/build.gradle"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "Prompt",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "e41d2b36-8c47-4417-9b63-9e610f3b8d0b",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "ok some fremeworks has github link and we dont need scrap?"
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "timestamp": 1781778898
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "144b5018-7821-40b8-9e44-e0f565949acb",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "\n\nGood point. Many frameworks keep their docs as Markdown files in GitHub repos, so we can fetch them directly from GitHub raw content instead of scraping HTML sites. This is more reliable (no HTML parsing, no anti-scraping blocks) and gives cleaner text.\n\nHere's which frameworks have docs in GitHub:\n\n| Framework | GitHub Docs Location |\n|-----------|---------------------|\n| Go Fiber | `gofiber/docs` repo (markdown) |\n| Quarkus | `quarkusio/quarkusio.github.io` (guides as .adoc) |\n| Actix-web | `actix/actix-web` /docs or website repo |\n| Rocket | `rwf2/Rocket` /docs (markdown) |\n| NestJS | `nestjs/docs.nestjs.com` (markdown) |\n| Express | `expressjs/expressjs.com` (markdown) |\n| Gin | `gin-gonic/website` (markdown) |\n| Echo | `labstack/echox` (website markdown) |\n| Axum | docs.rs (generated from source, not markdown) |\n| FastAPI | `tiangolo/fastapi` /docs (markdown) |\n| Django | `django/django` /docs (reStructuredText) |\n| Flask | `pallets/flask` /docs (reStructuredText) |\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Add a GitHub markdown fetcher** (uses raw.githubusercontent.com to pull `.md` files directly — no HTML parsing needed)\n2. **Convert the scrapers** that have GitHub-hosted docs to use that approach instead\n\nThis would replace HTML scraping with direct markdown download for frameworks like Go Fiber, FastAPI, NestJS, Express, Gin, Echo, and Rocket. The remaining ones (Spring, ASP.NET/Microsoft Learn, Django/Flask with .rst) would still need HTML scraping.\n\nShould I proceed with this approach?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "Prompt",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "f9303e59-cc3c-47c3-b26e-7da79329514f",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "yes"
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "timestamp": 1781778923
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "5f679986-a0a5-4eb4-873f-8f007ab5c72b",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": ""
          },
          {
            "kind": "toolUse",
            "data": {
              "toolUseId": "tooluse_f82mVjlpaDxyEROGk7q1XK",
              "name": "write",
              "input": {
                "__tool_use_purpose": "Create GitHub markdown fetcher base class",
                "command": "create",
                "content": "import httpx\nfrom ..scraper import BaseScraper, DocPage\n\n\nclass GitHubDocsScraper(BaseScraper):\n    \"\"\"Base scraper that fetches markdown files directly from GitHub repos.\"\"\"\n\n    repo: str  # e.g. \"gofiber/docs\"\n    branch: str = \"main\"\n    paths: list[str] = []  # e.g. [\"docs/guide/routing.md\"]\n    source: str = \"\"\n    version: str = \"\"\n    language: str = \"\"\n    topics_prefix: str = \"\"\n    categories: str = \"\"\n\n    def scrape(self) -> list[DocPage]:\n        pages = []\n        client = httpx.Client(timeout=30, follow_redirects=True)\n        base = f\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{self.repo}/{self.branch}\"\n\n        for path in self.paths:\n            url = f\"{base}/{path}\"\n            try:\n                resp = client.get(url)\n                if resp.status_code != 200:\n                    continue\n                text = resp.text.strip()\n                if len(text) < 100:\n                    continue\n\n                # Extract title from first heading\n                title = path.split(\"/\")[-1].replace(\".md\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \" \").title()\n                for line in text.split(\"\\n\"):\n                    if line.startswith(\"# \"):\n                        title = line[2:].strip()\n                        break\n\n                section = path.split(\"/\")[-1].replace(\".md\", \"\")\n                github_url = f\"https://github.com/{self.repo}/blob/{self.branch}/{path}\"\n\n                pages.append(DocPage(\n                    url=github_url, title=title, section_title=section,\n                    text=text, source=self.source, version=self.version,\n                    language=self.language,\n                    topics=self.topics_prefix + \",\" + section.replace(\"-\", \",\"),\n                    categories=self.categories,\n                ))\n            except Exception:\n                continue\n        client.close()\n        return pages\n",
                "path": "/Users/ekoosha/projects/tutorial/mcp-doc/ingestion/src/scrapers/github_base.py"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    },
