        "message_id": "d3b7b49e-0a5e-4bda-9ccb-0d0476fd9fb8",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Done. Here's what changed:\n\n**New `GitHubDocsScraper` base class** (`scrapers/github_base.py`) — fetches raw markdown from `raw.githubusercontent.com`, no HTML parsing needed.\n\n**Converted to GitHub-based scrapers:**\n| Scraper | GitHub Repo | Format |\n|---------|------------|--------|\n| Go Fiber | `gofiber/docs` | Markdown |\n| Go Gin | `gin-gonic/gin` | Markdown |\n| Go Echo | `labstack/echox` | Markdown |\n| FastAPI | `fastapi/fastapi` | Markdown |\n| Express | `expressjs/expressjs.com` | Markdown |\n| NestJS | `nestjs/docs.nestjs.com` | Markdown |\n| Rocket | `rwf2/Rocket` | Markdown |\n| Actix-web | `actix/actix-web` | Markdown |\n\n**Still using HTML scraping** (no clean GitHub markdown available):\n- Spring Boot, Spring Framework, Spring Security, Spring Data, Spring Cloud (Asciidoc rendered to HTML)\n- ASP.NET Core / C# Minimal API (Microsoft Learn)\n- Django, Flask (reStructuredText)"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "Prompt",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "ff4e3606-63d4-4ccb-b2ab-48b3319336eb",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "are you sure  Spring Boot, Spring Framework, Spring Security, Spring Data, Spring Cloud (Asciidoc rendered to HTML)\n  - ASP.NET Core / C# Minimal API (Microsoft Learn)\n  - Django, Flask (reStructuredText)\n  does not have github docs?"
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "timestamp": 1781779041
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "2eca95d3-306a-465d-b8c3-2150455d5a9b",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "You're right to push back. Let me check — they actually do have docs in GitHub:\n\n| Framework | GitHub Repo | Format |\n|-----------|------------|--------|\n| Spring Boot | `spring-projects/spring-boot` /spring-boot-project/spring-boot-docs/src/docs/asciidoc/ | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Framework | `spring-projects/spring-framework` /framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/ | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Security | `spring-projects/spring-security` /docs/modules/ROOT/pages/ | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Data JPA | `spring-projects/spring-data-jpa` /spring-data-jpa/src/main/antora/modules/ROOT/pages/ | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Cloud | `spring-cloud/spring-cloud-gateway` etc. various repos | Asciidoc |\n| ASP.NET Core | `dotnet/AspNetCore.Docs` /aspnetcore/ | Markdown ✓ |\n| Django | `django/django` /docs/ | reStructuredText |\n| Flask | `pallets/flask` /docs/ | reStructuredText |\n\nSo **ASP.NET is actually Markdown on GitHub** — no scraping needed. The Spring ones are Asciidoc (still readable as plain text, just has `=` headings and some markup). Django/Flask are `.rst` but still plain text.\n\nAll of these can be fetched raw from GitHub. The `GitHubDocsScraper` will work for all of them — Asciidoc and RST are text-based and chunk fine without parsing HTML.\n\nWant me to convert all of them to GitHub-based fetching?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "Prompt",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "70ede73c-a230-4ea7-a605-6da192b14f8f",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "yes"
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "timestamp": 1781779056
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
