        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Done. All scrapers now use **GitHub raw content fetching** — no HTML scraping anywhere:\n\n| Scraper | GitHub Repo | Format |\n|---------|------------|--------|\n| Go Fiber | `gofiber/docs` | Markdown |\n| Go Gin | `gin-gonic/gin` | Markdown |\n| Go Echo | `labstack/echox` | Markdown |\n| FastAPI | `fastapi/fastapi` | Markdown |\n| Express | `expressjs/expressjs.com` | Markdown |\n| NestJS | `nestjs/docs.nestjs.com` | Markdown |\n| Rocket | `rwf2/Rocket` | Markdown |\n| Actix-web | `actix/actix-web` | Markdown |\n| Django | `django/django` | RST (plain text) |\n| Flask | `pallets/flask` | RST (plain text) |\n| ASP.NET Core | `dotnet/AspNetCore.Docs` | Markdown |\n| Spring Boot | `spring-projects/spring-boot` | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Framework | `spring-projects/spring-framework` | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Security | `spring-projects/spring-security` | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Data | `spring-projects/spring-data-jpa` | Asciidoc |\n| Spring Cloud | `spring-cloud/spring-cloud-gateway` | Asciidoc |\n\nAll formats (Markdown, RST, Asciidoc) are plain text and chunk cleanly without HTML parsing. The `GitHubDocsScraper` base class handles them all identically."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
