        "message_id": "5ca33808-b582-4788-92e3-b4a74e5a79a8",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "**All 16 scrapers working end-to-end.** Here's the summary:\n\n| Framework | Pages | Chunks | SQL Size |\n|-----------|-------|--------|----------|\n| Go Fiber | 2 | 311 | 1.5 MB |\n| Go Gin | 1 | 207 | 1.0 MB |\n| Go Echo | 1 | 31 | 154K |\n| FastAPI | 2 | 65 | 328K |\n| Express | 1 | 31 | 154K |\n| NestJS | 1 | 76 | 382K |\n| Rocket | 2 | 198 | 990K |\n| Actix-web | 1 | 15 | 75K |\n| Django | 2 | 117 | 588K |\n| Flask | 2 | 112 | 564K |\n| ASP.NET Core | 2 | 442 | 2.2 MB |\n| Spring Boot | 2 | 209 | 1.0 MB |\n| Spring Framework | 2 | 69 | 348K |\n| Spring Security | 2 | 182 | 932K |\n| Spring Data | 1 | 114 | 581K |\n| Spring Cloud | 2 | 8 | 41K |\n\n**Total: ~2,187 chunks** across all frameworks — enough to test the full pipeline (fetch → chunk → embed → SQL). The pipeline is validated and ready. You can now scale up the `paths` lists in each scraper to pull in more documentation pages."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
