      "data": {
        "message_id": "af369d12-b009-4e30-9bb8-1e9bcdcb6f5e",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Based on the PRD milestones, the next step is **building and testing the Docker image** with the MCP server + PostgreSQL running together. Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Build the Quarkus MCP server JAR** — requires Java 25 and Maven\n2. **Build the Docker image** — packages PostgreSQL + pgvector + JRE + server JAR + pre-generated SQL\n3. **Test the MCP tool** — send a JSON-RPC request via stdin to verify search works\n\n```bash\n# 1. Build the server\n./mvnw package -DskipTests -Dquarkus.package.jar.type=uber-jar\n\n# 2. Build Docker image\ndocker build -t framework-docs-mcp:latest .\n\n# 3. Test it\necho '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"searchDocs\",\"arguments\":{\"query\":\"fiber routing\"}}}' \\\n  | docker run -i --rm framework-docs-mcp:latest\n```\n\nDo you want me to proceed with building the server JAR? (You'll need Java 25 installed — should I check if it's available on your system?)"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
