    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "2d0292c6-3ecf-47bd-9a94-fbcfdbed11de",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "The server starts and immediately stops because it's in stdio mode — with `docker run -d`, there's no stdin to keep it alive. The logs show everything works:\n\n- ✅ PostgreSQL initialized with pgvector\n- ✅ **2187 document chunks indexed**\n- ✅ Quarkus MCP server started in 0.315s\n- ✅ Embedding model loading\n\nThe server stops because stdio mode exits when stdin is closed. This is correct behavior for MCP — it only stays alive when connected to a client. Let me test it properly with a pipe:"
          },
          {
            "kind": "toolUse",
            "data": {
              "toolUseId": "tooluse_vWE139PM3UnBw6b3glKjMr",
              "name": "shell",
              "input": {
                "__tool_use_purpose": "Test MCP protocol properly - send initialize request, keep stdin open briefly",
                "command": "cd /Users/ekoosha/projects/tutorial/mcp-doc && docker rm -f mcp-test 2>/dev/null; (echo '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"initialize\",\"params\":{\"protocolVersion\":\"2024-11-05\",\"capabilities\":{},\"clientInfo\":{\"name\":\"test\",\"version\":\"1.0\"}}}'; sleep 30) | docker run -i --rm --name mcp-test framework-docs-mcp:latest 2>/dev/null &\nPID=$!\nsleep 20\nkill $PID 2>/dev/null\nwait $PID 2>/dev/null"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    },
