    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "ed36f3e0-2983-42e5-806a-76869bcaf91b",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "**Complete end-to-end test successful!** Here's the full verification:\n\n```\n✅ Python ingestion: 16 scrapers → 2,187 chunks embedded → SQL files generated\n✅ Quarkus MCP server: builds successfully (uber-jar)\n✅ Docker image: builds with PostgreSQL 17 + pgvector + Java 25 + server\n✅ PostgreSQL init: loads all 2,187 chunks + creates ivfflat index\n✅ MCP protocol: initialize handshake works\n✅ searchDocs tool: returns relevant results (score 0.845 for routing, 1.049 for spring-security with filter)\n✅ Framework filtering: spring-security filter returns only Spring Security docs\n```\n\nThe image starts PostgreSQL, loads data, and serves MCP queries — all inside a single container. To use it with any AI agent:\n\n```bash\n# Claude Code\nclaude mcp add framework-docs -- docker run -i --rm framework-docs-mcp:latest\n\n# VS Code / Cursor\n# args: [\"run\", \"-i\", \"--rm\", \"framework-docs-mcp:latest\"]\n```"
          },
          {
            "kind": "toolUse",
            "data": {
              "toolUseId": "tooluse_CPT1F5ie1V7zyysmRhRQae",
              "name": "shell",
              "input": {
                "__tool_use_purpose": "Clean up test containers",
                "command": "docker rm -f mcp-test framework-docs-test-pg 2>/dev/null; echo \"Cleaned up\""
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    },
