    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "dec9d3d1-41d5-40d5-b077-090608a2b0e8",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Currently the chunker uses **fixed-size character splitting** with `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter`:\n\n```python\nchunk_size=500, chunk_overlap=50,\nseparators=[\"\\n## \", \"\\n### \", \"\\n\\n\", \"\\n\", \". \", \" \"]\n```\n\nIt tries to split at markdown headers first (`##`, `###`), then paragraphs, then sentences, then words — but ultimately it just aims for ~500 character chunks regardless of semantic meaning.\n\n**The problem with this approach:**\n- A section about \"routing\" might get split into 3 chunks, losing context\n- A chunk might contain the tail of one topic and the start of another\n- Headers get separated from their content\n\n**Better approaches:**\n\n1. **Header-based (semantic sections)** — split at `# / ## / ###` boundaries, keeping each section as one chunk (with max size limit). Each chunk = one complete topic.\n\n2. **Topic-aware** — parse the markdown structure, keep header + its body together, and only split further if a section exceeds max size.\n\n3. **Hybrid** — split by headers first, then if a section is too large, subdivide it using the recursive character splitter.\n\nOption 3 is the best for our use case. Want me to rewrite the chunker to be header-aware? It would:\n- Parse markdown headers to identify sections\n- Keep `## Section Title` + its body as one chunk\n- Only split large sections (>1000 chars) further using character splitting\n- Preserve the section title as a prefix in sub-chunks for context"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "Prompt",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "7797113e-086c-4298-b1e1-e338707c180a",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "yes  Option 3"
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "timestamp": 1781780356
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "d2e527cb-8d78-49a6-b675-232d0b534d59",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": ""
          },
          {
            "kind": "toolUse",
            "data": {
              "toolUseId": "tooluse_jJSczbnTvQKhHijUF6ny37",
              "name": "write",
              "input": {
                "__tool_use_purpose": "Rewrite chunker with header-aware hybrid approach",
                "command": "create",
                "content": "import re\nfrom langchain_text_splitters import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\nfrom .scraper import DocPage\n\nMAX_CHUNK = 1000\nMIN_CHUNK = 50\n\n_sub_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n    chunk_size=500, chunk_overlap=50,\n    separators=[\"\\n\\n\", \"\\n\", \". \", \" \"]\n)\n\n# Matches markdown (#), asciidoc (= or ==), and rst (underlines) headers\n_HEADER_RE = re.compile(r\"^(#{1,4}\\s+.+|={1,5}\\s+.+)$\", re.MULTILINE)\n\n\ndef _split_by_headers(text: str) -> list[tuple[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"Split text into (section_title, body) pairs by headers.\"\"\"\n    sections = []\n    lines = text.split(\"\\n\")\n    current_title = \"\"\n    current_body = []\n\n    for line in lines:\n        if _HEADER_RE.match(line.strip()):\n            # Save previous section\n            if current_body:\n                body = \"\\n\".join(current_body).strip()\n                if body:\n                    sections.append((current_title, body))\n            current_title = line.strip().lstrip(\"#=\").strip()\n            current_body = []\n        else:\n            current_body.append(line)\n\n    # Last section\n    if current_body:\n        body = \"\\n\".join(current_body).strip()\n        if body:\n            sections.append((current_title, body))\n\n    return sections\n\n\ndef chunk_page(page: DocPage) -> list[tuple[str, dict]]:\n    sections = _split_by_headers(page.text)\n\n    # If no headers found, treat whole text as one section\n    if not sections:\n        sections = [(\"\", page.text)]\n\n    chunks = []\n    for section_title, body in sections:\n        if len(body) <= MAX_CHUNK:\n            # Keep as single chunk\n            chunk_text = f\"{section_title}\\n\\n{body}\" if section_title else body\n            chunks.append(chunk_text)\n        else:\n            # Split large sections, prefix sub-chunks with section title\n            sub_chunks = _sub_splitter.split_text(body)\n            for sub in sub_chunks:\n                chunk_text = f\"{section_title}\\n\\n{sub}\" if section_title else sub\n                chunks.append(chunk_text)\n\n    metadata = {\n        \"source\": page.source, \"version\": page.version,\n        \"language\": page.language, \"title\": page.title,\n        \"section_title\": page.section_title, \"url\": page.url,\n        \"topics\": page.topics, \"categories\": page.categories,\n    }\n\n    return [(chunk, metadata) for chunk in chunks if len(chunk.strip()) >= MIN_CHUNK]\n",
                "path": "/Users/ekoosha/projects/tutorial/mcp-doc/ingestion/src/chunker.py"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    },
