        "message_id": "366c3a56-5744-4e66-98fd-3911ced7434b",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "All tests pass with the new header-aware chunker. Summary:\n\n**New chunking strategy (hybrid):**\n1. Split text at markdown/asciidoc headers (`#`, `##`, `###`, `=`, `==`)\n2. If a section ≤ 1000 chars → keep it whole\n3. If a section > 1000 chars → subdivide at paragraphs/sentences (~500 char sub-chunks)\n4. Every sub-chunk gets its **section title prefixed** so it retains context\n\n**Result:** 2,049 chunks (vs 2,187 before) — fewer, more semantically coherent chunks that each represent a complete topic or sub-topic."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
