        "message_id": "c2c95fd0-89a1-4727-8812-a037e8b70f69",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "It found **Spring Framework** `beans/definition.adoc` — which covers bean definitions and DI. But the results are about XML config, not `@Autowired` annotations specifically.\n\n**Why?** Our test data for Spring Framework only includes:\n- `core/beans/definition.adoc` — bean XML definitions\n- `web/webmvc.adoc` — web MVC\n\nWe're missing the key file: `core/beans/annotation-config.adoc` (or `dependencies.adoc`) which covers `@Autowired`. This is exactly the limitation of our minimal test set — we only have 2 files per framework.\n\nTo get proper `@Autowired` results, we'd need to add `framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/beans/dependencies.adoc` or the annotation-config page to the Spring Framework scraper's paths list. That's the expected behavior — the search works correctly, we just don't have that specific documentation indexed yet."
          }
        ]
      }
