            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Same issue — it returns `definition.adoc` content about bean creation, not about scopes. The actual scope documentation lives in `core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc` which we don't have indexed.\n\nOur minimal Spring Framework test data:\n- ✅ `core/beans/definition.adoc` — bean definitions, factory methods\n- ✅ `web/webmvc.adoc` — web MVC\n- ❌ `core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc` — **singleton, prototype, request, session scopes**\n- ❌ `core/beans/dependencies.adoc` — **@Autowired, constructor injection**\n- ❌ `core/beans/annotation-config.adoc` — **@Component, @Service, etc.**\n\nThe search engine works — it just doesn't have the right docs. Want me to add more Spring Framework pages so these queries return proper results?"
